Insurance

Company Overview of Harel Insurance Investments & Financial Services Ltd



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Harel Insurance Investments & Financial Services Ltd., through its subsidiaries, operates as a multi-line insurance company in Israel, Germany, the United Kingdom, France, Switzerland, and the United States. It operates through five segments: Life Assurance and Long-Term Savings, Health Insurance, Non-life insurance, Insurance Companies Overseas, and Capital Market and Financial Services. The company offers various classes of life insurance products, which provides coverage for risks, such as death, disability, work disability, and critical illness; provides long-term saving products; and manages pension and provident funds. It also provides health insurance that provides coverage for outpat...
Harel Insurance Investments & Financial Services Ltd., through its subsidiaries, operates as a multi-line insurance company in Israel, Germany, the United Kingdom, France, Switzerland, and the United States. It operates through five segments: Life Assurance and Long-Term Savings, Health Insurance, Non-life insurance, Insurance Companies Overseas, and Capital Market and Financial Services. The company offers various classes of life insurance products, which provides coverage for risks, such as death, disability, work disability, and critical illness; provides long-term saving products; and manages pension and provident funds. It also provides health insurance that provides coverage for outpatient medical expenses, hospitalizations, lump sum compensation for dread diseases, health insurance for travelers, long term care, and personal accidents; vehicle and liabilities insurance services; fire and theft, home, business premises, goods in transit, electronic equipment, mechanical failure, and contractors’ insurance services, as well as biker’s and wedding insurance services; mortgage insurance services; and credit insurance services. In addition, the company manages mutual funds; provides investment services and manages investment portfolios for private customers, corporations, and institutional customers in capital markets; manages exchange traded notes with a range of local and foreign stocks and bond indexes; offers index-linked and deposit certificates on various currencies; provides consulting services in foreign currency; and trades in securities. Further, it invests in real estate assets, such as shopping malls and power centers, office buildings, high streets retail, student's accommodation, multifamily residential, and light industrial and development schemes. The company was founded in 1933 and is based in Ramat Gan, Israel.
Detailed Description


