Harel Insurance and Finance Group























Company Background
Harel Insurance Investments & Financial Services Ltd can be traced back to 1935, and as well as being one of Israel's largest insurance and financial services groups is also the second largest insurer with an overall market share of 20%. Harel was placed first among Israel's largest insurance companies in a comprehensive service survey run by the Association of Insurance Agents and Brokers published at the beginning of 2012 which found them to offer the best possible service in the fields of life, pension, health and long-term care.
Harel Group leads the market in the field of health insurance with a market share of over 40% and has total Group assets under management for insurance, pension funds, provident funds, mutual funds and financial services totaling over NIS 146.4 billion as of June 30 2013.


