Income statement (ILA)Year on year Harel Insurance Investments and Financial Services Ltd had net income fall -12.95% from 455.59m to 396.60m despite a 10.10% increase in revenues from 12.20bn to 13.43bn. An increase in the selling, general and administrative costs as a percentage of sales from 24.09% to 24.88% was a component in the falling net income despite rising revenues.FT Lexicon{0}{0}{2}{0}{0}{2}For more information, visit the FT LexiconLexicon on this pageExplore our toolsAlertsData archivePortfolioWorld marketsEquities screenerFunds overview



